1
00:00:05,379 --> 00:00:07,566
<i>The human body
is a terrible liar.</i>

2
00:00:07,732 --> 00:00:09,581
<i>Whatever secrets
it's keeping,</i>

3
00:00:10,003 --> 00:00:12,340
<i>it will tell them all
eventually.</i>

4
00:00:13,839 --> 00:00:15,065
You back at work?

5
00:00:15,893 --> 00:00:17,668
- No.
- You gonna be?

6
00:00:18,035 --> 00:00:19,528
I had to meet with
Koracick to ask.

7
00:00:19,616 --> 00:00:20,871
He's not sure.

8
00:00:20,967 --> 00:00:22,675
Yeah, well,
I guess it was pretty sudden.

9
00:00:22,763 --> 00:00:24,308
You did kinda
screw him.

10
00:00:24,597 --> 00:00:27,285
And we don't all have parents
who can clean up our messes.

11
00:00:28,981 --> 00:00:30,488
You coming tonight?

12
00:00:30,576 --> 00:00:31,863
Why wouldn't I be coming?

13
00:00:31,951 --> 00:00:33,731
Well, seeing as
you can't stand the sight of me,

14
00:00:33,818 --> 00:00:35,137
I thought
maybe you'd skip it.

15
00:00:35,558 --> 00:00:39,050
Jackson, my opinion of you
has no effect on my plans.

16
00:00:39,138 --> 00:00:40,552
It's Richard and Catherine's
anniversary.

17
00:00:40,639 --> 00:00:42,332
I care about them.
I'm going.

18
00:00:42,474 --> 00:00:44,793
And you're clearly
in the mood to celebrate,

19
00:00:44,904 --> 00:00:47,003
so,
that's great.

20
00:00:47,304 --> 00:00:50,898
<i>Leprosy, chicken pox,
tuberculosis, HIV...</i>

21
00:00:50,986 --> 00:00:54,166
We can carry these for years
with no physical symptoms.

22
00:00:55,948 --> 00:00:57,726
I'm sorry you drove
all the way out here,

23
00:00:57,814 --> 00:00:59,385
but my answer is no.

24
00:00:59,473 --> 00:01:01,096
This isn't only
your decision.

25
00:01:01,184 --> 00:01:02,549
And this dinner
is ridiculous.

26
00:01:02,637 --> 00:01:04,090
We're giving them
big news.

27
00:01:04,178 --> 00:01:05,211
It affects us all.

28
00:01:05,299 --> 00:01:06,632
Yeah, so we should just
tell them.

29
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:08,057
Richard,
I care about Maggie.

30
00:01:08,145 --> 00:01:09,432
I know you care
about Jackson.

31
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:11,564
This dinner is for them,
not for us.

32
00:01:11,652 --> 00:01:12,877
We're still gonna
be a family,

33
00:01:12,965 --> 00:01:14,510
even if you and I
are separating.

34
00:01:14,598 --> 00:01:16,869
<i>But given enough time,
the signs will always show up.</i>

35
00:01:16,957 --> 00:01:19,197
Can't wait for this
damn night to be over.

36
00:01:19,285 --> 00:01:20,336
- Hey.
- Hi!

37
00:01:20,424 --> 00:01:21,742
- Hey!
- Hi, guys!

38
00:01:21,830 --> 00:01:23,150
- Hi. Mwah.
- Hi.

39
00:01:23,238 --> 00:01:25,321
How you been? Mwah.

40
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,379
So, u-um,
all set for tonight?

41
00:01:28,434 --> 00:01:30,092
Hey, I'm making
blackberry cobbler.

42
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:31,024
Ooh, my favorite.

43
00:01:31,112 --> 00:01:32,323
Yum!

44
00:01:32,410 --> 00:01:35,033
<i>The real question is,
what are your body's secrets?</i>

45
00:01:35,121 --> 00:01:38,002
So, um...
see you soon.

46
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:39,682
- Oh, I can't wait.
- Yeah, yeah.

47
00:01:39,778 --> 00:01:40,675
- Alright, see you tonight.
- Okay.

48
00:01:40,763 --> 00:01:41,828
Okay.
See you tonight.

49
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,471
<i>And are you ready to know?</i>

50
00:01:48,258 --> 00:01:50,463
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 16  Episode 12</font>

51
00:01:51,321 --> 00:01:53,580
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"The Last Supper"</font>

52
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,947
I can reach
for my own water.

53
00:02:02,408 --> 00:02:04,613
The hospital just wants me
to rest a few more weeks.

54
00:02:04,701 --> 00:02:06,991
There's nothing wrong with me
helping you with that.

55
00:02:12,356 --> 00:02:15,059
Now that...
That makes me feel better.

56
00:02:15,155 --> 00:02:16,808
Is everybody decent?

57
00:02:16,895 --> 00:02:19,073
Except for the ball gag
and jock strap, we're good.

58
00:02:19,161 --> 00:02:20,704
- Levi.
- What was that, honey?

59
00:02:20,792 --> 00:02:21,955
What do you need, Mom?

60
00:02:22,043 --> 00:02:23,456
Cousin Shirl just called

61
00:02:23,544 --> 00:02:25,776
to say that Mayda heard
that Great Uncle Saul

62
00:02:25,864 --> 00:02:28,088
is circling the drain
over at Olympia Meadows...

63
00:02:28,176 --> 00:02:29,245
"Circling the drain"?

64
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:32,378
You couldn't say that like...
I don't know, like a person?

65
00:02:32,466 --> 00:02:34,329
If he had behaved
more like a person...

66
00:02:34,475 --> 00:02:36,243
Other than with you...
Then maybe.

67
00:02:36,331 --> 00:02:39,143
The point is,
he's in hospice,

68
00:02:39,231 --> 00:02:41,054
so if you want to see him,
then...

69
00:02:41,142 --> 00:02:42,549
Now?

70
00:02:43,158 --> 00:02:44,691
A-A-As in now-now?

71
00:02:44,779 --> 00:02:47,215
As in, try not to get a ticket
speeding on the interstate.

72
00:02:47,303 --> 00:02:48,636
That's up to you.

73
00:02:48,799 --> 00:02:49,885
Bring a sweater, honey.

74
00:02:49,973 --> 00:02:51,784
Those places
are like an icebox.

75
00:02:58,230 --> 00:02:59,565
You okay?

76
00:03:01,283 --> 00:03:04,495
Uncle Saul was an ass
to everyone else.

77
00:03:05,803 --> 00:03:07,018
I have no idea why,

78
00:03:07,106 --> 00:03:09,979
but it's like life gave him
45% of being a good man,

79
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,948
and he spent it all
on me.

80
00:03:18,423 --> 00:03:20,290
Happy anniversary, guys.

81
00:03:20,550 --> 00:03:22,540
Anniversary.
Um...

82
00:03:22,938 --> 00:03:25,721
I suppose it is
in a few days, isn't it?

83
00:03:25,809 --> 00:03:27,925
That's not why you invited us
over for dinner tonight?

84
00:03:28,012 --> 00:03:29,085
Not exactly.

85
00:03:29,173 --> 00:03:30,620
You know,
when you get to be our age,

86
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:32,417
you stop counting, dear.

87
00:03:32,505 --> 00:03:34,362
- Here, give me this coat.
- Yes. Here.

88
00:03:34,487 --> 00:03:37,174
So, um, a patient
turned me on to those.

89
00:03:37,262 --> 00:03:39,581
They are insane.
They're French.

90
00:03:39,731 --> 00:03:41,777
You shouldn't have. 
Really.

91
00:03:44,112 --> 00:03:45,966
- Is something wrong?
- Oh, no.

92
00:03:46,053 --> 00:03:46,966
- Of course not.
- Okay.

93
00:03:47,053 --> 00:03:48,161
Mm-hmm.

94
00:03:48,864 --> 00:03:49,981
- Oh. Well...
- Oh.

95
00:03:50,069 --> 00:03:51,488
Alright.

96
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:55,675
Happy anniversary.

97
00:03:55,763 --> 00:03:57,579
Oh, thank you.

98
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:58,784
Um, more gifts.

99
00:03:58,872 --> 00:04:00,073
- More... Wonderful.
- Jackson,

100
00:04:00,161 --> 00:04:01,971
- is this an Alice Mann?
- Yes, it is.

101
00:04:02,059 --> 00:04:03,230
She only printed three of those.

102
00:04:03,317 --> 00:04:04,731
Oh! Sorry I didn't have
time to get it gift-wrapped.

103
00:04:04,818 --> 00:04:06,433
I literally just got it back
from the framer,

104
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,977
and it took forever to get it
out of South Africa.

105
00:04:09,065 --> 00:04:10,885
Jackson,
you are just...

106
00:04:11,096 --> 00:04:12,471
- Mm.
- ..too much.

107
00:04:12,559 --> 00:04:14,352
South Africa.
Nice.

108
00:04:15,423 --> 00:04:17,018
Uh,
is that a problem?

109
00:04:17,106 --> 00:04:18,139
No, I just wish I'd known

110
00:04:18,227 --> 00:04:19,472
you were bringing
something so expensive.

111
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:20,762
I brought chocolates.

112
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:22,224
Oh, well,
who doesn't love chocolate?

113
00:04:22,311 --> 00:04:23,844
I love chocolate.

114
00:04:23,932 --> 00:04:25,961
Come on, Maggie.
Let's go have some chocolate.

115
00:04:31,071 --> 00:04:32,224
Don't like it?

116
00:04:32,312 --> 00:04:34,260
Oh, no, no.
It's beautiful.

117
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:36,305
Uh, she's mom's favorite,

118
00:04:36,393 --> 00:04:38,112
and I figured you guys have
similar taste.

119
00:04:38,294 --> 00:04:39,496
You know,
I could help you find a spot

120
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,369
- to hang it up if you want.
- Um, n-n-n-not yet.

121
00:04:41,456 --> 00:04:42,807
Um...

122
00:04:43,752 --> 00:04:46,229
- Come on in.
- Sure, yeah.

123
00:04:53,035 --> 00:04:55,596
Dinner should be
ready shortly.

124
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,250
Um, we wanted to
talk about...

125
00:04:58,338 --> 00:05:00,612
I wonder, who would like
a glass of wine?

126
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,443
- I know I surely do.
- Uh, heavy, please.

127
00:05:02,531 --> 00:05:03,968
- Me, please.
- Okay.

128
00:05:04,974 --> 00:05:06,010
Oh.

129
00:05:06,428 --> 00:05:10,385
So, Mom, they set an opening
for the hospital at Memphis?

130
00:05:10,473 --> 00:05:11,476
Early next month.

131
00:05:11,579 --> 00:05:12,902
So many hospitals.

132
00:05:12,990 --> 00:05:14,903
I do not know how
you keep track of them all.

133
00:05:14,991 --> 00:05:16,194
By never being at home.

134
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:20,503
By hiring good people
who help me run things.

135
00:05:20,675 --> 00:05:22,468
Tom Koracick excluded,
I guess.

136
00:05:22,574 --> 00:05:24,088
He's very good
at what he does.

137
00:05:24,176 --> 00:05:26,526
You know, now that
we are all together,

138
00:05:26,614 --> 00:05:28,488
- what we wanted to talk with you...
- I think that we could really wait

139
00:05:28,575 --> 00:05:30,721
until we've all
eaten, dear.

140
00:05:30,809 --> 00:05:33,807
I don't know
if it needs to wait, hon.

141
00:05:35,076 --> 00:05:36,659
What's wrong?

142
00:05:37,411 --> 00:05:39,245
- Did you get bad news?
- Oh, God no.

143
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,049
My scans
have come back great.

144
00:05:41,137 --> 00:05:43,417
Richard,
you're terrifying them.

145
00:05:45,014 --> 00:05:46,806
Oh, that must be Vic.

146
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:48,432
Who's Vic?
His girlfriend.

147
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,370
I came from work,
so she's meeting me here.

148
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:52,291
- But why?
- Good question.

149
00:05:52,394 --> 00:05:54,477
You invited your girlfriend
to our dinner?

150
00:05:54,565 --> 00:05:55,924
More, the merrier, right?

151
00:05:59,683 --> 00:06:00,886
Hello!

152
00:06:00,973 --> 00:06:02,183
Hey.

153
00:06:03,025 --> 00:06:05,346
Uh, you need a ride
or something?

154
00:06:05,434 --> 00:06:06,471
Oh, no, I invited him.

155
00:06:06,559 --> 00:06:07,765
That's okay, right?

156
00:06:07,853 --> 00:06:09,082
You said it's a party.

157
00:06:09,170 --> 00:06:10,389
Dinner... Dinner party.

158
00:06:10,477 --> 00:06:11,316
I said it was
a dinner

159
00:06:11,404 --> 00:06:12,271
- party.
- Didn't hear that part.

160
00:06:12,367 --> 00:06:13,756
Mm-hmm.
What did you do?

161
00:06:14,076 --> 00:06:15,402
Come on in, man.
Don't worry about it.

162
00:06:15,489 --> 00:06:16,893
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Welcome.

163
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:18,093
Alright.

164
00:06:22,370 --> 00:06:24,144
Dean Miller.
Pleasure to meet you.

165
00:06:24,232 --> 00:06:25,553
Richard Webber.
Pleasure's mine.

166
00:06:25,641 --> 00:06:27,055
- Please, please, have a seat.
- Hi.

167
00:06:27,142 --> 00:06:28,675
Richard,
I want you to meet Vic.

168
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,060
Oh, hello.

169
00:06:30,148 --> 00:06:31,131
It's so nice
to meet you.

170
00:06:31,219 --> 00:06:32,390
Jackson's told me
so much about you.

171
00:06:32,477 --> 00:06:35,240
And I'm sure Mom's told you
plenty about Vic.

172
00:06:35,448 --> 00:06:37,428
Oh, yes, yeah.
Right?

173
00:06:37,553 --> 00:06:38,636
Yes.

174
00:06:40,381 --> 00:06:43,748
So, this is a really small
dinner party, huh?

175
00:06:43,901 --> 00:06:46,350
Well, it's a good thing
I made plenty of food.

176
00:06:46,438 --> 00:06:47,681
Um, Richard,

177
00:06:47,769 --> 00:06:49,972
would you mind giving me a hand
in the kitchen?

178
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,940
- I was just about to ask.
- Mm.

179
00:06:58,005 --> 00:07:00,207
I, uh, feel like
we're crashing.

180
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:02,553
- No.
- Why would you think that?

181
00:07:03,302 --> 00:07:05,865
Well, you're not crashing...
At all, actually.

182
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,600
Let me go ahead
and grab you some wine.

183
00:07:08,272 --> 00:07:09,885
See if Maggie's
left us any.

184
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,045
Uncle Saul.

185
00:07:23,322 --> 00:07:27,395
Boy, do you look like
a steaming pile of crap, kid.

186
00:07:27,483 --> 00:07:29,212
Same to you,
Uncle Saul.

187
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:30,709
Thought you were
his favorite.

188
00:07:31,162 --> 00:07:33,053
Insults is how
we show love.

189
00:07:33,373 --> 00:07:35,545
I'm assuming you're Levi,
the doctor.

190
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:37,488
I've heard
a lot about you.

191
00:07:37,576 --> 00:07:38,803
How is he?

192
00:07:38,891 --> 00:07:40,675
He's in end-stage
heart failure,

193
00:07:40,763 --> 00:07:42,889
so we're doing our best
to keep him comfortable.

194
00:07:43,183 --> 00:07:45,926
Which, I've learned,
does not include

195
00:07:46,013 --> 00:07:48,596
an all-expense paid trip
to Maui.

196
00:07:48,683 --> 00:07:51,326
I'm afraid not,
Saul, no.

197
00:07:51,414 --> 00:07:52,965
I'll come back
to check on you later.

198
00:07:53,053 --> 00:07:54,420
Meh.

199
00:07:54,623 --> 00:07:56,060
Thank you.

200
00:07:56,325 --> 00:07:58,309
- Boychick.
- Da.

201
00:08:00,205 --> 00:08:01,794
Mm.

202
00:08:02,605 --> 00:08:06,348
- We had Shabbat dinner last week...
- Ah.

203
00:08:06,568 --> 00:08:11,111
..and I snuck a few
hard-boiled eggs in my pocket,

204
00:08:11,206 --> 00:08:12,864
thinking you'd show up,

205
00:08:13,091 --> 00:08:15,278
but the nurse
sniffed 'em out

206
00:08:15,457 --> 00:08:17,000
and trashed 'em.

207
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:19,950
He always knew
they were my favorite.

208
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:21,776
Where's Aunt Gertie?

209
00:08:22,052 --> 00:08:23,929
Eh, Gertie makes it
when she can.

210
00:08:24,017 --> 00:08:26,090
I tell her don't bother,
but she says,

211
00:08:26,209 --> 00:08:29,020
"That's what you do
for the man you love."

212
00:08:30,096 --> 00:08:33,174
Saul, this is Nico.
I wanted you to meet him...

213
00:08:33,262 --> 00:08:34,885
What's this I hear
about you living

214
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:36,768
- in your mother's basement?
- Ugh.

215
00:08:36,856 --> 00:08:38,595
I thought you
were a hot-shot doctor.

216
00:08:38,736 --> 00:08:40,239
I was hoping that

217
00:08:40,327 --> 00:08:41,934
we would iron
a few things out

218
00:08:42,053 --> 00:08:43,731
before I just
up and left.

219
00:08:43,941 --> 00:08:45,630
I hate to move out
on bad terms.

220
00:08:45,718 --> 00:08:47,631
My nephew,
King of Vague.

221
00:08:47,719 --> 00:08:50,972
Spill. I don't have time
to play guessing games.

222
00:08:51,060 --> 00:08:54,433
Mom learned some new
information about me,

223
00:08:54,524 --> 00:08:56,575
which was all
well and good

224
00:08:56,685 --> 00:08:58,434
as long as I kept it
in house.

225
00:08:58,522 --> 00:09:00,294
You think I'm getting
on a roof

226
00:09:00,393 --> 00:09:02,630
with a bugle horn
anytime soon?

227
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:04,622
Excellent point.

228
00:09:05,435 --> 00:09:07,848
Well, Uncle Saul.

229
00:09:08,795 --> 00:09:12,200
Nico here is
more than my friend.

230
00:09:12,581 --> 00:09:15,005
H-He's my boyfriend.

231
00:09:15,574 --> 00:09:20,309
And he has been
for a while now, and...

232
00:09:20,849 --> 00:09:21,889
I love him.

233
00:09:23,495 --> 00:09:25,528
It's an honor to
meet you, sir.

234
00:09:28,353 --> 00:09:30,806
Oh, God.
Dr. Marks!

235
00:09:44,378 --> 00:09:45,856
I killed him.

236
00:09:46,486 --> 00:09:48,239
I killed him
with my gayness.

237
00:09:54,991 --> 00:09:57,704
Did you know they were
bringing dates to dinner?

238
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:59,145
Of course not.

239
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,613
Well, we can't
tell them now.

240
00:10:00,701 --> 00:10:01,865
Yeah, well, if you'd have
listened to me,

241
00:10:01,952 --> 00:10:03,684
we'd have told them
without the fanfare.

242
00:10:03,772 --> 00:10:05,559
Well, it's too late
for that.

243
00:10:06,065 --> 00:10:07,575
We'll just
tell them later.

244
00:10:07,995 --> 00:10:11,184
Let's just get try to
get through tonight.

245
00:10:11,534 --> 00:10:13,052
Yep.

246
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:14,997
I've gotten good
at that.

247
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:25,677
Um, any... any, uh, good, like,
calls, uh, recently?

248
00:10:25,830 --> 00:10:26,927
Something cool?

249
00:10:27,022 --> 00:10:31,325
Oh, there was a C.O.
buildup in the sewer yesterday.

250
00:10:31,591 --> 00:10:33,919
Shot some manhole covers
straight up in the air.

251
00:10:34,007 --> 00:10:37,135
