325
00:14:05,591 --> 00:14:07,292
I'm not doing this
with you right now.

326
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,803
Think whatever you want.

327
00:14:08,891 --> 00:14:10,844
I wasn't trying to
set you up, Maggie.

328
00:14:10,932 --> 00:14:12,515
I don't know why you'd even leap
to something like that

329
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:14,374
if you didn't think
the world revolved around you.

330
00:14:14,461 --> 00:14:15,459
I leapt to it

331
00:14:15,547 --> 00:14:17,616
because he has already
asked me out before.

332
00:14:17,959 --> 00:14:19,131
What?

333
00:14:19,506 --> 00:14:20,765
When? Recently?

334
00:14:20,853 --> 00:14:22,162
No. Months ago.

335
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,756
So, like,
when we were together?

336
00:14:23,844 --> 00:14:26,530
Yeah, while you were
on your nature walk-about,

337
00:14:26,618 --> 00:14:29,006
sending me
pictures of trees.

338
00:14:29,365 --> 00:14:31,725
Should I have
sent you a picture of him

339
00:14:31,927 --> 00:14:34,380
with that, like,
shrugging "why not?" emoji?

340
00:14:37,528 --> 00:14:40,108
Well, he's here now.

341
00:14:40,223 --> 00:14:42,556
We might as well
be hospitable.

342
00:14:44,195 --> 00:14:47,108
I don't think you got to worry
about Jackson and his ex.

343
00:14:47,264 --> 00:14:49,000
Unless you're worried about
them murdering each other.

344
00:14:49,087 --> 00:14:50,410
Mm.

345
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:52,287
Well, that's good.

346
00:14:52,631 --> 00:14:54,635
You'll be all set up for your
second chance with her.

347
00:14:54,722 --> 00:14:56,256
Yeah, she's real thrilled
to see me.

348
00:14:56,344 --> 00:14:59,436
Um, did you even consider maybe
telling her I was coming?

349
00:14:59,927 --> 00:15:01,129
Oh, yeah,

350
00:15:01,217 --> 00:15:03,350
but then she probably
would have bailed.

351
00:15:03,588 --> 00:15:05,400
Mm-hmm. And then you wouldn't be
having dinner

352
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:07,042
with your boyfriend's ex.

353
00:15:07,486 --> 00:15:09,303
Time to eat!

354
00:15:09,567 --> 00:15:10,998
Well,
it's too late now, so...

355
00:15:17,238 --> 00:15:18,465
Oh, actually,
my mom usually sits here,

356
00:15:18,552 --> 00:15:19,530
so we'll just...

357
00:15:19,618 --> 00:15:22,331
Sit. Sit. It's fine.
Nobody cares.

358
00:15:22,431 --> 00:15:24,993
Nobody cares 
about anything.

359
00:15:25,854 --> 00:15:28,424
Everybody sit.
Please.

360
00:15:32,549 --> 00:15:34,419
Smells great in there.
What'd you make?

361
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:37,350
Shrimp scampi.

362
00:15:37,564 --> 00:15:39,505
Is there a problem?
Are you allergic?

363
00:15:39,593 --> 00:15:40,494
Vic?
No.

364
00:15:40,582 --> 00:15:42,495
She'll put anything
in her mouth.

365
00:15:46,762 --> 00:15:48,255
Anything...
Anything that's food.

366
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:49,796
Only food.

367
00:15:50,384 --> 00:15:52,697
Hm.
How lovely.

368
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:55,790
- A little salad, dear, please?
- Thank you.

369
00:15:56,004 --> 00:15:57,307
Let me tell you
about that time

370
00:15:57,395 --> 00:15:59,479
she stopped a snake
from eating a baby.

371
00:16:04,526 --> 00:16:06,487
So, Dr. Webber,
you're Maggie's father.

372
00:16:06,575 --> 00:16:08,112
Call me Richard, please.

373
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,846
And yes, I am.

374
00:16:10,237 --> 00:16:12,610
And Dr. Fox...
Or do you prefer Catherine?

375
00:16:13,142 --> 00:16:14,619
Dr. Fox is fine.

376
00:16:15,009 --> 00:16:17,056
Okay.
You're Jackson's mother?

377
00:16:17,231 --> 00:16:19,322
Uh, pass the bread,
please.

378
00:16:20,511 --> 00:16:22,322
Yes.
I'm Jackson's mother.

379
00:16:22,878 --> 00:16:24,541
So, when you two
started dating,

380
00:16:24,629 --> 00:16:26,385
was that before
they got married?

381
00:16:26,473 --> 00:16:28,135
Not really, no.

382
00:16:28,449 --> 00:16:30,344
We never thought of
ourselves as family.

383
00:16:30,432 --> 00:16:31,174
Yes, you did.

384
00:16:31,262 --> 00:16:32,236
That's why I had
such a reaction

385
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:34,026
when the two of you started
rolling around together.

386
00:16:34,113 --> 00:16:35,844
No, Mom.

387
00:16:36,027 --> 00:16:38,158
We were happy for them.

388
00:16:38,246 --> 00:16:39,019
- Hm.
- Mm.

389
00:16:39,107 --> 00:16:40,729
Thank you.

390
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,166
Jackson and I
didn't grow up together.

391
00:16:43,284 --> 00:16:45,830
We had very different
upbringings.

392
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:46,565
