and he had a private chauffeur.

394
00:16:48,991 --> 00:16:50,074
Dean's
a rich boy, too.

395
00:16:50,162 --> 00:16:51,486
Oh, are you?

396
00:16:51,597 --> 00:16:53,198
Maggie doesn't like guys
that have money.

397
00:16:53,286 --> 00:16:55,041
No, I like the ones
who are down to earth.

398
00:16:56,059 --> 00:16:57,764
So, Maggie,
you grew up in Boston?

399
00:16:57,852 --> 00:16:58,643
Mm-hmm.

400
00:16:58,731 --> 00:17:00,338
I have a cousin
in Brighton.

401
00:17:00,426 --> 00:17:01,736
Oh, yeah?
What street?

402
00:17:01,824 --> 00:17:04,510
I don't remember.
There were old brick houses.

403
00:17:04,598 --> 00:17:05,801
- Does that help?
- Yeah.

404
00:17:05,889 --> 00:17:07,144
Yeah, that really
narrows it down.

405
00:17:10,166 --> 00:17:11,502
Oh, you know what?

406
00:17:11,590 --> 00:17:13,543
You remember
the Korean restaurant we loved,

407
00:17:13,631 --> 00:17:15,244
uh, near my old place
on Graham?

408
00:17:15,332 --> 00:17:16,432
- Mm-hmm.
- It burned down.

409
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:17,683
Vic saved the owner,

410
00:17:17,771 --> 00:17:18,901
pulled him right out
of the kitchen.

411
00:17:18,988 --> 00:17:20,283
He was
the sweetest old man.

412
00:17:20,371 --> 00:17:21,533
He got really shaken up.

413
00:17:21,678 --> 00:17:22,666
Apparently, the landlord

414
00:17:22,754 --> 00:17:25,307
